                <componentInstanceProperties>
                    <name>richTextValue</name>
                    <value>&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;background-color: var(--slds-g-color-neutral-base-100, var(--lwc-colorBackgroundInput,rgb(255, 255, 255))); color: var(--slds-g-color-neutral-base-30, var(--lwc-colorTextWeak,rgb(116, 116, 116))); font-family: var(--lwc-fontFamily,-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &apos;Segoe UI&apos;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &apos;Apple Color Emoji&apos;, &apos;Segoe UI Emoji&apos;, &apos;Segoe UI Symbol&apos;); font-size: var(--lwc-fontSize3,0.8125rem);&quot;&gt;Simply add Users to Permission Set - Apex Pulse to enable the access to all the components of apexPulse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: var(--slds-g-color-neutral-base-100, var(--lwc-colorBackgroundInput,rgb(255, 255, 255))); color: var(--slds-g-color-neutral-base-30, var(--lwc-colorTextWeak,rgb(116, 116, 116))); font-family: var(--lwc-fontFamily,-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &apos;Segoe UI&apos;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &apos;Apple Color Emoji&apos;, &apos;Segoe UI Emoji&apos;, &apos;Segoe UI Symbol&apos;); font-size: var(--lwc-fontSize3,0.8125rem);&quot;&gt;ï»¿Instructions on h&lt;/span&gt;ow to add users to permission set are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--lwc-fontFamily,-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &apos;Segoe UI&apos;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &apos;Apple Color Emoji&apos;, &apos;Segoe UI Emoji&apos;, &apos;Segoe UI Symbol&apos;); font-size: var(--lwc-fontSize3,0.8125rem); color: var(--slds-g-color-neutral-base-30, var(--lwc-colorTextWeak,rgb(116, 116, 116))); background-color: var(--slds-g-color-neutral-base-100, var(--lwc-colorBackgroundInput,rgb(255, 255, 255)));&quot;&gt;1. Navigate to Permission Sets&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Settings&lt;/strong&gt;: Click on the gear icon at the top right corner and select &quot;Setup.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quick Find&lt;/strong&gt;: In the left sidebar, use the Quick Find box to search for &quot;Permission Sets.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Select Permission Sets&lt;/strong&gt;: Click on &quot;Permission Sets&quot; under &quot;Users.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. Choose the Permission Set&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;List of Permission Sets&lt;/strong&gt;: You&apos;ll see a list of all available permission sets.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Select Permission Set&lt;/strong&gt;: Click on the name of the permission set you want to assign to the user.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. Manage Assignments&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage Assignments&lt;/strong&gt;: In the selected permission set&apos;s detail page, click on the &quot;Manage Assignments&quot; button.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;4. Add Assignments&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Add Assignments&lt;/strong&gt;: Click on the &quot;Add Assignments&quot; button.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Select Users&lt;/strong&gt;: You will see a list of users. Check the box next to the names of the users you want to add to the permission set.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assign&lt;/strong&gt;: Click on the &quot;Assign&quot; button to add the selected users to the permission set.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;5. Confirm and Finish&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Confirmation&lt;/strong&gt;: You will see a confirmation message indicating the users have been successfully assigned to the permission set.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Finish&lt;/strong&gt;: Click &quot;Done&quot; to complete the process.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now, the selected users have been added to the permission set and will have the permissions defined by that set.&lt;/p&gt;</value>
